# Configuration Files

## gentoo-update.conf.example

Example configuration file for Gentoo-Update.

Location: `~/.config/gentoo-update/gentoo-update.conf`

To generate a default config, run:
```bash
gentoo-update --gen-config
```

### Configuration Format

```ini
# Disable colored output
NoColor=false

# Always show full output
AlwaysShow=false

# Number of news items to display (default: 5)
NewsNum=5

# Number of old package versions to keep (default: 3)
KeepOldPackages=3

# Keep installed package binaries (default: 0)
KeepInstalledPackages=0

# Program to use for showing config file diffs (default: vimdiff)
DiffProg=vimdiff

# Interval between tray checks in seconds (default: 3600 = 1 hour)
CheckInterval=3600

# Automatically sync repositories before checking (default: true)
AutoSync=true

# Check for packages needing preserved rebuild (default: true)
CheckPreservedRebuild=true

# Check for kernel updates (default: true)
CheckKernelUpdates=true

# Check for configuration files needing updates (default: true)
CheckConfigFiles=true

# Check distfiles for cleanup (default: true)
CheckDistfiles=true
```

Each setting is optional and uses the specified default if not present.
